
---


@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes
class University {
}

class Department {
}

class ResearchGroup {
    - name: String
    - department: Department
}

class Researcher {
    - name: String
    - researchGroup: ResearchGroup
}

class Project {
    - title: String
}

class WorkPackage {
    - name: String
    - project: Project
    - leader: ResearchGroup
}

class TeamAssignment {
    - startDate: Date
    - endDate: Date
    - researcher: Researcher
    - workPackage: WorkPackage
}

' Relationships
University "1" o-- "many" Department
Department "1" *-- "many" ResearchGroup
ResearchGroup "1" *-- "many" Researcher
Project "1" *-- "many" WorkPackage
WorkPackage "1" --> "1" ResearchGroup : hasLeader
WorkPackage "1" *-- "many" TeamAssignment
TeamAssignment "1" --> "1" Researcher
TeamAssignment "1" --> "1" WorkPackage

@enduml

---

### 🧩 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **University**: Top-level container for departments.
- **Department**: Contains multiple `ResearchGroups`.
- **ResearchGroup**: A group of researchers. Each researcher belongs to exactly one group.
- **Researcher**: Assigned to WPs regardless of which RG leads them. Must be linked via `TeamAssignment`.
- **Project**: Composed of multiple `WorkPackages`.
- **WorkPackage (WP)**: Belongs to a project and is led by a `ResearchGroup`. Can have multiple team members from any group.
- **TeamAssignment**: Captures the assignment of a researcher to a WP, including start and end dates for traceability.

---

### 🔄 Notes on Service Delivery Tracking:
- The `TeamAssignment` class ensures that all assignments are time-bound and traceable.
- If a researcher changes groups or a WP leadership changes, old `TeamAssignments` are closed (end date set), and new ones are created with updated links.

